The paper deals with graph theory and algorithms for deciding properties of graphs, which are typically categorized under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The concept of tree-decomposability is also relevant to computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also involves logic and complexity theory, which are covered under cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
